stly melted.", "img": "https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f1/Melt-Butter-Step-11.jpg/v4-460px-Melt-Butter-Step-11.jpg", "vid": null}, "12": {"text": "Stir to melt remaining pieces.", "img": "https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/ec/Melt-Butter-Step-12.jpg/v4-460px-Melt-Butter-Step-12.jpg", "vid": null}, "13": {"text": "Know how to tell when butter is soft.", "img": "https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/0b/Melt-Butter-Step-13.jpg/v4-460px-Melt-Butter-Step-13.jpg", "vid": null}, "14": {"text": "Cut butter into pieces before softening.", "img": "https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/ae/Melt-Butter-Step-14.jpg/v4-460px-Melt-Butter-Step-14.jpg", "vid": null}, "15": {"text": "Leave butter on the counter near the oven.", "img": "https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f5/Melt-Butter-Step-15.jpg/v4-460px-Melt-Butter-Step-15.jpg", "vid": null}, "16": {"text": "Soften butter more quickly by mashing or beating it.", "img": "https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/16/Melt-Butter-Step-16.jpg/v4-460px-Melt-Butter-Step-16.jpg", "vid": null}, "17": {"text": "Place a container of butter in a warm water bath.", "img": "https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/58/Melt-Butter-Step-17.jpg/v4-460px-Melt-Butter-Step-17.jpg", "vid": null}, "18": {"text": "Rapidly soften frozen butter by grating it.", "img": "https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/57/Melt-Butter-Step-18.jpg/v4-460px-Melt-Butter-Step-18.jpg", "vid": null}}